1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:49,404 --> 00:00:52,073
STILL SHINING

3
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:06,045
MARCH 2021

4
00:01:07,005 --> 00:01:08,256
Hello, sir.

5
00:01:09,841 --> 00:01:11,676
You don't have to bow like that
with our team.

6
00:01:13,303 --> 00:01:14,304
Okay.

7
00:01:15,388 --> 00:01:17,849
Dawn is a good time for programming.

8
00:01:18,850 --> 00:01:19,851
It's quiet.

9
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:35,450
As for Grandma and Grandpa,

10
00:01:36,743 --> 00:01:38,202
they're so happy I got a job

11
00:01:38,828 --> 00:01:41,456
that they're always picking up tabs
for people in town.

12
00:01:43,499 --> 00:01:44,626
And Hui-seo…

13
00:01:47,253 --> 00:01:48,338
He's even more thrilled.

14
00:01:49,255 --> 00:01:50,673
He's always saying he's happy.

15
00:01:51,925 --> 00:01:53,384
I've never seen someone

16
00:01:54,052 --> 00:01:56,012
who says that out loud.

17
00:01:57,972 --> 00:01:59,557
I thought it was just a word.

18
00:02:04,312 --> 00:02:05,438
It's peculiar.

19
00:02:08,107 --> 00:02:09,150
As for me…

20
00:02:12,487 --> 00:02:13,738
Well…

21
00:02:16,241 --> 00:02:18,076
Does it even matter?

22
00:02:24,249 --> 00:02:31,214
STILL SHINING

23
00:02:34,217 --> 00:02:36,719
The train is now approaching.

24
00:02:37,595 --> 00:02:42,058
SEPTEMBER 2025

25
00:02:51,985 --> 00:02:53,027
In position.

26
00:02:59,325 --> 00:03:01,452
Doors opened. Screen doors opened.

27
00:03:18,428 --> 00:03:19,971
The doors are closing.

28
00:03:20,888 --> 00:03:22,306
The doors are closing.

29
00:03:22,390 --> 00:03:24,142
The screen doors are closing.

30
00:03:30,064 --> 00:03:31,274
TRAIN OPERATOR 231
YEON TAE-SEO

31
00:03:38,364 --> 00:03:39,866
Hello.

32
00:03:39,949 --> 00:03:40,992
-Tae-seo, over here.
-Hey.

33
00:03:41,075 --> 00:03:42,744
-I'm off.
-Hey, Tae-seo. You're going?

34
00:03:42,827 --> 00:03:43,661
-Last train?
-Yeah.

35
00:03:44,245 --> 00:03:46,247
At least we saw each other. See you later.

36
00:03:46,331 --> 00:03:48,541
-Good luck.
-Bye. Good luck.

37
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,960
-Ma'am, I…
-We ordered for you.

38
00:03:53,046 --> 00:03:55,715
-Do you want a drink?
-I'm on the 6:01 a.m. train tomorrow.

39
00:03:55,798 --> 00:03:56,966
I have to leave right after.

40
00:03:58,051 --> 00:04:00,470
I know we eat fast for work,
but slow down, man.

41
00:05:11,332 --> 00:05:12,667
When did you get here?

42
00:05:13,209 --> 00:05:16,212
I was going to see Mi-ju after doing
errands for Dad, but she's busy.

43
00:05:16,796 --> 00:05:18,047
Geez. I'm hungry.

44
00:05:18,131 --> 00:05:19,632
Let's make some ramyeon.

45
00:05:19,715 --> 00:05:22,927
I forgot to hook up the gas.
You know I don't cook at home.

46
00:05:23,511 --> 00:05:25,304
You've forgotten for three years. Geez.

47
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:27,390
My goodness.

48
00:05:28,850 --> 00:05:30,810
Sure. It happens.

49
00:05:31,436 --> 00:05:32,812
It's whatever you want, after all.

50
00:05:39,652 --> 00:05:41,195
This is too much.

51
00:05:41,279 --> 00:05:43,823
Sure. I guess it's okay to live like this.

52
00:05:45,158 --> 00:05:46,784
What is this?

53
00:06:02,967 --> 00:06:04,260
It can be a bit loud.

54
00:06:09,932 --> 00:06:12,185
It's too loud to do this at night.

55
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:15,354
Hey, why do you live like this?

56
00:06:27,909 --> 00:06:29,118
See you later.

57
00:06:31,579 --> 00:06:33,039
Quit looking at me like that.

58
00:06:33,122 --> 00:06:35,166
-Don't point at me. Do this.
-Go.

59
00:06:42,465 --> 00:06:45,927
Why are you telling me
to attend Mr. Mu's sister's wedding?

60
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:47,470
You should go.

61
00:06:47,553 --> 00:06:49,138
You know I don't have weekends off.

62
00:06:49,222 --> 00:06:50,598
Come on.

63
00:06:51,265 --> 00:06:53,476
You always say you're busy
and never drop by.

64
00:06:55,102 --> 00:06:56,979
Let me know if anything's broken.

65
00:06:57,063 --> 00:06:58,439
I'll come right away to fix it.

66
00:06:58,522 --> 00:07:02,276
Does something have to break
for you to come home?

67
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,779
Don't you feel sorry for me?

68
00:07:04,862 --> 00:07:07,281
Honestly, I don't ever
bother you or anything

69
00:07:07,365 --> 00:07:10,284
while I take care of Grandma and Grandpa.

70
00:07:10,368 --> 00:07:12,828
Why are you always busy
whenever I call you?

71
00:07:12,912 --> 00:07:14,288
Here it goes again.

72
00:07:14,372 --> 00:07:16,207
If you were busy dating,
then it'd be fine.

73
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:18,167
But you need to see someone
to get married.

74
00:07:18,251 --> 00:07:20,044
Then, I can have nieces and nephews.

75
00:07:20,127 --> 00:07:22,547
That way, I can become an awesome uncle.

76
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:24,048
How about having three kids?

77
00:07:24,131 --> 00:07:26,384
-I'm hanging up.
-What? Hello--

78
00:07:29,428 --> 00:07:31,597
PLAYLIST

79
00:08:14,432 --> 00:08:18,769
YOUR ACCOUNT IS CURRENTLY STREAMING
ON A DIFFERENT DEVICE

80
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,751
YOUR ACCOUNT IS STREAMING
ON A DIFFERENT DEVICE

81
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:28,214
STOP OTHER DEVICE
AND STREAM ON THIS DEVICE?

82
00:09:28,297 --> 00:09:29,131
CANCEL

83
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,842
The train is now approaching.

84
00:09:40,726 --> 00:09:41,894
It's Eun-a.

85
00:09:43,187 --> 00:09:46,107
DONGJAK STATION

86
00:10:25,730 --> 00:10:27,565
-Ms. Mo Eun-a?
-Yes.

87
00:10:27,648 --> 00:10:29,191
Please come up this way.

88
00:10:31,569 --> 00:10:34,864
Most of our guests are solo travelers.

89
00:10:34,947 --> 00:10:38,367
Many of them are writers
who stay here for long periods.

90
00:10:38,909 --> 00:10:42,413
You need to ask the long-term guests
for housekeeping hours.

91
00:10:42,496 --> 00:10:44,915
And we outsource the cleaning
to another company.

92
00:10:47,001 --> 00:10:49,044
This is our new manager.

93
00:10:56,469 --> 00:10:59,180
-Here's the inventory list.
-Okay.

94
00:10:59,263 --> 00:11:01,974
Make sure to clock out at 4:10 p.m. sharp.

95
00:11:02,057 --> 00:11:04,435
Our boss said you were a veteran

96
00:11:04,518 --> 00:11:07,396
and emphasized that I had to remind you
of when to clock out.

97
00:11:08,314 --> 00:11:11,317
We inform guests on the booking page
that this is an unmanned hotel,

98
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,444
but there are always a few
who complain in reviews.

99
00:11:13,527 --> 00:11:16,280
So please remind them when they check in.

100
00:11:17,031 --> 00:11:18,574
Also,

101
00:11:18,657 --> 00:11:21,619
you need to wear
white tops and black bottoms.

102
00:11:21,702 --> 00:11:24,538
You just need to get the colors right.
Did you bring your clothes?

103
00:11:24,622 --> 00:11:26,874
Yes. What about the manuals?

104
00:11:26,957 --> 00:11:28,584
I put all of them up on the monitor.

105
00:11:29,627 --> 00:11:32,087
-And the break room?
-This way.

106
00:11:44,225 --> 00:11:46,060
This is the break room.

107
00:11:49,438 --> 00:11:51,815
-I'll put this here for now.
-Okay.

108
00:11:51,899 --> 00:11:53,776
I wanted to look around the area.

109
00:11:55,903 --> 00:11:58,030
I heard you ran a guesthouse before.

110
00:11:58,113 --> 00:11:59,073
Where was it?

111
00:12:00,241 --> 00:12:01,450
What happened?

112
00:12:07,373 --> 00:12:09,542
At least you got to run your own business.

113
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:13,045
-Have you found a place to live?
-I had to leave in a hurry, so…

114
00:12:13,587 --> 00:12:15,297
My place is really nice.

115
00:12:15,381 --> 00:12:18,467
My roommate is great too.
And I'm moving out in two weeks.

116
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:21,011
It's close by. I highly recommend it.

117
00:12:21,679 --> 00:12:23,847
I'm telling you because you seem nice.

118
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,849
Could I get your number?

119
00:13:40,591 --> 00:13:41,967
It's been a while.

120
00:13:52,936 --> 00:13:54,104
Hey.

121
00:13:58,651 --> 00:14:00,486
Eun-a.

122
00:14:00,569 --> 00:14:02,112
How have you been?

123
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:05,741
Let's go.

124
00:14:05,824 --> 00:14:07,701
Go.

125
00:14:07,785 --> 00:14:09,203
I'm so happy.

126
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:12,581
What is it?

127
00:14:21,799 --> 00:14:22,841
My dad's photo.

128
00:14:28,347 --> 00:14:29,723
I came by to pick it up.

129
00:14:31,475 --> 00:14:32,935
You can take these bed sheets.

130
00:14:33,018 --> 00:14:33,852
They're new.

131
00:14:33,936 --> 00:14:35,479
Luxury hotels use them.

132
00:14:35,562 --> 00:14:36,855
You should use them.

133
00:14:37,773 --> 00:14:39,525
You'll need them if you're settling here.

134
00:14:40,109 --> 00:14:41,193
They look expensive.

135
00:14:41,276 --> 00:14:43,654
I shipped these to give them to you.

136
00:14:43,737 --> 00:14:46,115
I couldn't organize my things
since I left in a hurry.

137
00:14:46,198 --> 00:14:47,491
These were all I could grab.

138
00:14:52,204 --> 00:14:53,747
Are you hungry?

139
00:14:53,831 --> 00:14:54,707
Yeah.

140
00:14:57,668 --> 00:14:59,420
I didn't even get to visit Tongyeong.

141
00:15:00,504 --> 00:15:02,339
How can things happen like that?

142
00:15:02,423 --> 00:15:03,632
It's all over with.

143
00:15:03,716 --> 00:15:05,134
I'm actually relieved.

144
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:08,137
When I closed down the guesthouse,

145
00:15:08,220 --> 00:15:10,597
I was upset, dumbfounded,
and heartbroken for months.

146
00:15:11,181 --> 00:15:12,683
But I'm relieved to let it go.

147
00:15:20,357 --> 00:15:22,526
-Is this your mom's kimchi?
-Yeah.

148
00:15:22,609 --> 00:15:23,819
It's delicious.

149
00:15:23,902 --> 00:15:25,070
Eat up.

150
00:15:25,696 --> 00:15:27,114
You can have all of it.

151
00:15:29,158 --> 00:15:32,077
You can stay here
and take your time in finding a place.

152
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,873
Although it's a bit far,
you can commute from here.

153
00:15:35,956 --> 00:15:37,499
No, I don't need to stay here.

154
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:39,793
-I can sleep at my workplace.
-Since when?

155
00:15:39,877 --> 00:15:41,378
I'm pretty lucky.

156
00:15:41,462 --> 00:15:43,505
I found a job in Seoul
within a couple hours.

157
00:15:43,589 --> 00:15:45,549
My predecessor
connected me with her old place.

158
00:15:45,632 --> 00:15:49,136
And my acquaintance will suddenly be away
for a week, so she said to stay there.

159
00:15:49,219 --> 00:15:50,054
It's in Seoul.

160
00:15:51,138 --> 00:15:54,224
Everything's been going smoothly
after I decided to come to Seoul.

161
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,310
Still,

162
00:15:56,393 --> 00:15:59,730
if where you're staying isn't good,
you can come back here.

163
00:15:59,813 --> 00:16:01,065
Seung-jun said you could too.

164
00:16:05,944 --> 00:16:07,863
He's drunk again.

165
00:16:07,946 --> 00:16:10,115
I told him to come home early today.

166
00:16:10,199 --> 00:16:11,909
Why do you keep changing the passcode?

167
00:16:11,992 --> 00:16:13,744
Eun-a! You don't have to come out!

168
00:16:13,827 --> 00:16:16,121
Stay there, Eun-a! It's okay!

169
00:16:16,205 --> 00:16:17,414
You're so loud!

170
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:22,002
-I told you to come home early.
-Eun-a.

171
00:16:22,711 --> 00:16:23,670
Well…

172
00:16:23,754 --> 00:16:26,006
Look how we've all made it!

173
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:31,053
Middle schoolers from the country
have reunited in Seoul.

174
00:16:31,136 --> 00:16:32,429
This is Suwon.

175
00:16:33,388 --> 00:16:34,223
Have you been well?

176
00:16:34,306 --> 00:16:35,557
As if.

177
00:16:35,641 --> 00:16:39,394
Eun-a, you're the one
I envy the most in the world.

178
00:16:39,478 --> 00:16:40,521
Zip it and go away.

179
00:16:40,604 --> 00:16:42,231
-Do you know why? I'll tell you.
-Hurry.

180
00:16:42,314 --> 00:16:44,066
-Go wash your hands.
-You quit a job.

181
00:16:44,149 --> 00:16:45,609
-You stink.
-Then, you get a new one.

182
00:16:45,692 --> 00:16:47,069
You quit and get a new one.

183
00:16:47,152 --> 00:16:49,738
You go to all the great spots
like Namhae and Tongyeong.

184
00:16:49,822 --> 00:16:51,740
-Not to mention Hawaii, right?
-Go inside!

185
00:16:51,824 --> 00:16:55,327
I want to live freely too now!

186
00:16:55,994 --> 00:16:57,371
Geez, will you zip it?

187
00:16:58,539 --> 00:17:00,332
It's been a while since we've seen her…

188
00:17:03,127 --> 00:17:07,172
This stop is Dongjak.

189
00:17:07,256 --> 00:17:10,467
The doors are on your right.

190
00:17:26,817 --> 00:17:32,114
The doors are closing.

191
00:17:44,877 --> 00:17:49,798
The train for Buramsan is now approaching.

192
00:18:01,476 --> 00:18:02,895
May I have your attention, please?

193
00:18:02,978 --> 00:18:06,690
We will stand momentarily to maintain
proper distance between trains.

194
00:18:13,405 --> 00:18:16,158
SEONG-CHAN

195
00:18:33,091 --> 00:18:34,968
The doors are closing.

196
00:18:35,761 --> 00:18:39,139
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.
Train departing.

197
00:20:18,322 --> 00:20:21,366
I'll be staying in Seoul
for a bit starting today,

198
00:20:21,450 --> 00:20:23,618
just as you stayed
in Yeonwoo for a bit, Dad.

199
00:20:24,745 --> 00:20:25,829
I'll be in Seoul.

200
00:20:27,581 --> 00:20:28,874
Just for a moment too.

201
00:20:31,626 --> 00:20:34,546
-What was our room number?
-It's the room at the end.

202
00:21:06,286 --> 00:21:07,329
It's 13 millimeters.

203
00:21:08,163 --> 00:21:08,997
Thirteen.

204
00:21:35,941 --> 00:21:37,067
Hello?

205
00:21:39,027 --> 00:21:41,238
Sure. Got it. I'll change it.

206
00:21:41,780 --> 00:21:42,697
I forgot.

207
00:21:43,782 --> 00:21:44,783
Okay, bye.

208
00:21:44,866 --> 00:21:46,535
I had forgotten that I shared my account

209
00:21:48,328 --> 00:21:50,705
and the reason for sharing it.

210
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:53,583
I had forgotten all about it.

211
00:22:09,391 --> 00:22:10,892
-Hello.
-Hello.

212
00:22:10,976 --> 00:22:12,602
-Stay Youngwon?
-Yes.

213
00:22:13,103 --> 00:22:14,479
Here you go.

214
00:22:14,563 --> 00:22:16,064
-Thank you.
-Sure. Have a nice day.

215
00:22:16,148 --> 00:22:17,315
You too.

216
00:22:22,154 --> 00:22:23,738
Thank you for your work, ma'am.

217
00:22:24,948 --> 00:22:26,408
What's with the flowers?

218
00:22:27,325 --> 00:22:29,411
It's to celebrate my first day of work.

219
00:22:29,494 --> 00:22:31,079
Just for the first week.

220
00:22:31,163 --> 00:22:32,789
It's a personal ritual.

221
00:22:57,189 --> 00:23:01,067
This stop is Isu,
Chongshin University Station.

222
00:23:01,151 --> 00:23:02,527
The doors are on your right.

223
00:23:15,332 --> 00:23:16,583
In position.

224
00:23:17,375 --> 00:23:20,545
-The screen doors are opening.
-The doors are opening.

225
00:23:20,629 --> 00:23:22,672
Doors opened. Screen doors opened.

226
00:23:22,756 --> 00:23:25,592
Please watch your step.

227
00:23:25,675 --> 00:23:30,138
Train 4654, please stop
for an additional minute.

228
00:23:31,223 --> 00:23:33,725
This is Train 4654.
Request for stop is loud and clear.

229
00:23:36,728 --> 00:23:38,772
May I have your attention, please?

230
00:23:40,732 --> 00:23:42,859
To maintain proper distance
with the train ahead,

231
00:23:42,943 --> 00:23:47,030
we will be standing
for one minute before departing.

232
00:23:49,532 --> 00:23:50,700
Tae-seo.

233
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:32,409
Train 4654, you may depart now.

234
00:24:33,827 --> 00:24:37,247
The doors are closing.

235
00:24:57,726 --> 00:24:59,811
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.

236
00:25:00,603 --> 00:25:01,730
Train departing.

237
00:25:23,293 --> 00:25:28,840
Please watch your step.

238
00:25:47,025 --> 00:25:49,361
LAST TRAIN FOR OIDO
LAST TRAIN FOR ANSAN

239
00:25:57,911 --> 00:25:59,871
UNIT 610

240
00:26:03,166 --> 00:26:05,710
I'm on my way. I'm at Isu Station.

241
00:26:05,794 --> 00:26:09,381
Hey, that Seong-chan guy
called me out of the blue.

242
00:26:09,464 --> 00:26:12,133
After I told him
you were coming to my place today,

243
00:26:12,217 --> 00:26:14,302
I realized we'd be in trouble
if he barges in here.

244
00:26:16,221 --> 00:26:19,599
Na-yeong thinks we know each other
through Seong-chan.

245
00:26:19,682 --> 00:26:22,936
I told him you'd call me
when you got to Isu Station

246
00:26:23,019 --> 00:26:24,312
and we'd meet there.

247
00:26:24,396 --> 00:26:25,522
I just rambled on and on.

248
00:26:26,398 --> 00:26:28,274
He won't be waiting
for you there, will he?

249
00:26:31,277 --> 00:26:32,904
I'll call you back.

250
00:26:40,078 --> 00:26:41,663
What are you doing here?

251
00:26:43,456 --> 00:26:44,541
Eun-a.

252
00:26:51,589 --> 00:26:52,757
Let's go to Tongyeong.

253
00:26:52,841 --> 00:26:53,883
No.

254
00:26:54,884 --> 00:26:56,010
I told you I needed a break.

255
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:59,472
You disappeared after saying you'd go
and close down the guesthouse.

256
00:27:03,268 --> 00:27:04,936
The doors are opening.

257
00:27:26,624 --> 00:27:28,501
You have to know too!

258
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:55,361
Eun-a!

259
00:28:16,716 --> 00:28:17,717
Eun-a.

260
00:28:18,384 --> 00:28:19,761
Eun-a.

261
00:28:41,866 --> 00:28:43,159
Yeon Tae-seo.

262
00:29:12,105 --> 00:29:13,606
SEONG-CHAN

263
00:29:36,045 --> 00:29:38,298
We've been colleagues for ten years.

264
00:29:38,381 --> 00:29:40,341
Why be on a break
when we weren't even a thing?

265
00:29:41,217 --> 00:29:44,262
That way, you couldn't contact me
and deliver the bad news.

266
00:29:44,345 --> 00:29:46,973
We worked as partners,
so we should share the closure.

267
00:29:47,557 --> 00:29:49,392
Yes, we're colleagues. Happy now?

268
00:29:50,476 --> 00:29:51,978
It's their typical move.

269
00:29:52,061 --> 00:29:54,772
If business is good, they kick out
those running it and take over.

270
00:29:54,856 --> 00:29:56,983
We were duped by malicious outsiders.

271
00:29:57,066 --> 00:29:59,068
It wasn't your fault.
When we win the suit--

272
00:29:59,152 --> 00:30:00,320
So what's in it for us?

273
00:30:00,403 --> 00:30:01,821
We can't let them run…

274
00:30:04,991 --> 00:30:06,993
We can't let them do business either.

275
00:30:07,076 --> 00:30:09,579
It'll also be a loss for them
if the suit drags on.

276
00:30:09,662 --> 00:30:11,039
I'll see this through to the end.

277
00:30:12,999 --> 00:30:14,459
I really don't want to know.

278
00:30:15,293 --> 00:30:16,920
I don't want to hear about it.

279
00:30:25,929 --> 00:30:27,305
You've come so far.

280
00:30:28,473 --> 00:30:29,682
Why Seoul?

281
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:35,271
I'll visit often.

282
00:30:35,355 --> 00:30:38,816
Don't. I hate going back and forth
and matching schedules.

283
00:30:41,110 --> 00:30:42,987
The job here is simple and easy.

284
00:30:43,738 --> 00:30:45,365
It's great for passing the time.

285
00:30:45,448 --> 00:30:46,616
I feel comfortable.

286
00:30:52,914 --> 00:30:54,832
You've been through so much.

287
00:30:56,084 --> 00:30:57,835
Get home safely.

288
00:33:02,293 --> 00:33:03,503
Hello, Mr. Mu.

289
00:33:03,586 --> 00:33:06,130
Hey, why did you send
so much wedding gift money?

290
00:33:06,756 --> 00:33:07,799
It's nothing.

291
00:33:07,882 --> 00:33:10,093
I should've been there.

292
00:33:10,176 --> 00:33:11,803
You didn't have to come. You're busy.

293
00:33:11,886 --> 00:33:14,013
And Hui-seo was very helpful.

294
00:33:14,097 --> 00:33:17,725
He collected all the money at reception
and handed out the meal tickets.

295
00:33:17,809 --> 00:33:20,103
More students came than expected,
so it was hectic.

296
00:33:20,186 --> 00:33:21,979
But Hui-seo took care of everything.

297
00:33:22,063 --> 00:33:24,273
Did my classmates come too?

298
00:33:24,357 --> 00:33:26,192
To call them your classmates would be…

299
00:33:26,275 --> 00:33:28,361
The ones you might actually know…

300
00:33:28,444 --> 00:33:29,821
Eun-a…

301
00:33:30,530 --> 00:33:32,573
You haven't heard from her, have you?

302
00:33:33,324 --> 00:33:36,410
No. No one's heard anything from her.

303
00:33:36,494 --> 00:33:38,454
You're not in touch
with her either, right?

304
00:33:39,413 --> 00:33:40,790
No.

305
00:33:40,873 --> 00:33:42,208
Was it last month?

306
00:33:42,291 --> 00:33:44,585
A petition was filed under Eun-a's name.

307
00:33:45,294 --> 00:33:47,505
I heard a document
was filed very clumsily,

308
00:33:48,131 --> 00:33:50,758
requesting to tear down her house.

309
00:33:51,717 --> 00:33:54,011
As you know,
my wife works at the town office.

310
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:58,683
Demolishing a vacant house
requires a lot of complicated documents,

311
00:33:58,766 --> 00:34:02,311
but there was only one sheet of paper
with Eun-a's name on it.

312
00:34:07,608 --> 00:34:08,901
It came in the mail.

313
00:34:10,361 --> 00:34:11,946
This document is nonsense.

314
00:34:12,029 --> 00:34:14,907
Demolishing a vacant house
creates truckloads of trash,

315
00:34:14,991 --> 00:34:16,868
so it requires a delivery address.

316
00:34:16,951 --> 00:34:18,161
They wrote down Eun-a's house.

317
00:34:18,870 --> 00:34:22,456
So after demolishing the house,
did they want the trash piled there?

318
00:34:23,583 --> 00:34:25,668
There's no phone number, so I'm at a loss.

319
00:34:29,338 --> 00:34:30,173
Hey, Tae-seo!

320
00:34:30,256 --> 00:34:31,507
What on earth?

321
00:34:32,175 --> 00:34:33,009
That's my brother.

322
00:34:33,092 --> 00:34:34,427
-I see.
-Hey, Tae-seo!

323
00:34:34,510 --> 00:34:36,762
-He's the pride of Yeonwoo.
-Right.

324
00:34:36,846 --> 00:34:38,181
What brings you here?

325
00:34:38,264 --> 00:34:39,473
You should've told me.

326
00:34:39,557 --> 00:34:41,225
He's the one I always talked about.

327
00:34:41,309 --> 00:34:43,853
-My colleagues at the post office.
-Hello.

328
00:34:43,936 --> 00:34:46,856
-This is my mentor.
-Hui-seo's told me a lot about you.

329
00:34:51,068 --> 00:34:52,320
Why are you here?

330
00:34:54,864 --> 00:34:56,991
Three years ago,
you suddenly showed up on a weekday

331
00:34:57,783 --> 00:35:00,620
and dropped a bomb,
saying you quit that big company.

332
00:35:01,370 --> 00:35:02,705
Damn it, I'm still traumatized.

333
00:35:02,788 --> 00:35:05,625
You complain whether I come or not.

334
00:35:05,708 --> 00:35:06,667
How's work?

335
00:35:06,751 --> 00:35:08,878
The post office can't run without me.

336
00:35:08,961 --> 00:35:10,796
Didn't I tell you that already?

337
00:35:11,464 --> 00:35:13,466
Don't you worry about me.

338
00:35:14,842 --> 00:35:16,093
That is true.

339
00:35:17,178 --> 00:35:20,223
You'd been so responsible your whole life.
Why are you acting up now?

340
00:35:20,306 --> 00:35:22,391
You only do whatever you want.

341
00:35:22,475 --> 00:35:26,562
I never imagined
I'd worry about you when I grew up.

342
00:35:32,318 --> 00:35:35,071
Hey. Eat first. Okay?

343
00:35:35,154 --> 00:35:37,823
I couldn't prepare much
since you came without notice.

344
00:35:38,574 --> 00:35:41,452
I'll take care of this since I'm here.
Is there anything else?

345
00:35:41,535 --> 00:35:43,329
No. Just come and eat.

346
00:35:46,707 --> 00:35:48,042
Let's put this here.

347
00:35:48,125 --> 00:35:49,543
Grandpa is taking a while.

348
00:35:50,378 --> 00:35:53,464
He was a hard worker
when he worked on others' farms.

349
00:35:53,547 --> 00:35:56,550
Now that we have our own farm,
he basically lives there.

350
00:35:56,634 --> 00:35:58,636
It's good having our own farm, you know.

351
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:02,765
We get to live in comfort at this age
thanks to our grandsons.

352
00:36:03,849 --> 00:36:07,061
Goodness. I forgot the kimchi.
I'll go get it.

353
00:36:07,144 --> 00:36:10,106
-I'll go put this in the storage then.
-Okay.

354
00:36:41,679 --> 00:36:46,642
MART

355
00:37:14,295 --> 00:37:16,464
Yes? What is it?

356
00:37:18,132 --> 00:37:19,842
Gosh, look who it is.

357
00:37:20,593 --> 00:37:21,594
How have you been?

358
00:37:23,262 --> 00:37:24,680
Eun-a was here, right?

359
00:37:25,264 --> 00:37:27,433
These vegetable drawings are hers.

360
00:37:28,184 --> 00:37:29,185
She doesn't come here.

361
00:37:30,227 --> 00:37:31,604
Excuse me.

362
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,242
Please give this to her.

363
00:37:45,326 --> 00:37:46,744
010-0922-1109
YEON TAE-SEO

364
00:37:46,827 --> 00:37:49,080
I ran into her by chance in Seoul.

365
00:37:52,583 --> 00:37:55,211
Is Eun-a doing okay in Seoul?

366
00:37:56,462 --> 00:37:58,339
I don't think so.

367
00:37:59,924 --> 00:38:01,008
I only saw her by chance.

368
00:38:02,051 --> 00:38:04,929
You're wrong. She's fine.

369
00:38:10,226 --> 00:38:11,685
Here.

370
00:38:11,769 --> 00:38:14,939
She sends me Christmas cards every year.

371
00:38:15,022 --> 00:38:20,361
They were sent from hotels and hostels.
Those were places she worked.

372
00:38:21,278 --> 00:38:22,279
This one.

373
00:38:24,073 --> 00:38:25,366
It's from last year.

374
00:38:34,417 --> 00:38:36,419
Grandma, how have you been?

375
00:38:37,169 --> 00:38:40,256
I think I'll settle down here.

376
00:38:41,715 --> 00:38:43,008
She's been well.

377
00:38:53,060 --> 00:38:54,145
Stop.

378
00:38:55,229 --> 00:38:56,272
Let's stop…

379
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:58,941
with the worries and everything else.

380
00:39:00,276 --> 00:39:01,277
No more.

381
00:39:23,966 --> 00:39:26,469
I'm attaching the photo
since it can be disclosed.

382
00:39:26,552 --> 00:39:27,928
It's 5 by 7 inches.

383
00:39:28,012 --> 00:39:31,265
No glass. With at least 10 cm of margin.

384
00:39:32,183 --> 00:39:35,978
You can find Citizens' Cultural Heritage:
Old House online.

385
00:39:39,398 --> 00:39:41,108
I'LL FIND THE MEANING IF THE WORLD WON'T

386
00:39:41,192 --> 00:39:42,026
In order,

387
00:39:42,818 --> 00:39:46,280
they're oak, cherry, walnut, and maple.

388
00:39:47,156 --> 00:39:48,282
See how they would look.

389
00:39:51,577 --> 00:39:53,454
You can either leave margins

390
00:39:54,079 --> 00:39:56,332
or pull the frame in tighter.

391
00:40:01,128 --> 00:40:02,129
This one.

392
00:40:03,547 --> 00:40:06,091
Leaving margins would be nice.

393
00:40:06,175 --> 00:40:07,635
Can we use traditional paper?

394
00:40:07,718 --> 00:40:09,094
Yes, we can.

395
00:40:11,180 --> 00:40:12,389
What's your day job?

396
00:40:16,727 --> 00:40:17,895
I'm a train operator.

397
00:40:19,021 --> 00:40:20,481
I see.

398
00:40:20,564 --> 00:40:21,941
And you're not working today?

399
00:40:22,024 --> 00:40:24,151
I work tomorrow afternoon.
It's a night shift.

400
00:40:24,944 --> 00:40:26,820
A total of five. And your name?

401
00:40:28,280 --> 00:40:30,407
Im A-sol.

402
00:40:30,491 --> 00:40:32,034
Ms. Im A-sol.

403
00:40:33,369 --> 00:40:34,912
The type of wood is oak.

404
00:40:35,746 --> 00:40:37,081
By the third week…

405
00:40:38,582 --> 00:40:40,209
of next month. Is that right?

406
00:40:41,126 --> 00:40:42,962
What's good about being a train operator?

407
00:40:44,380 --> 00:40:45,506
Well…

408
00:40:46,882 --> 00:40:50,135
It's good because I can't bring work home.

409
00:40:51,178 --> 00:40:52,638
That's awesome.

410
00:40:52,721 --> 00:40:54,056
I have a question too.

411
00:40:54,765 --> 00:40:57,017
What made you decide
to commission me for this job?

412
00:40:57,601 --> 00:41:00,145
I've never done this for anyone
other than my colleagues.

413
00:41:01,063 --> 00:41:02,606
It was at a restaurant.

414
00:41:03,357 --> 00:41:07,945
A landscape photo had a frame worthy
of being in an art gallery, so I asked.

415
00:41:08,028 --> 00:41:10,489
And I checked the social media account
written on the back.

416
00:41:11,365 --> 00:41:14,451
Also, can I commission you
for another frame?

417
00:41:14,535 --> 00:41:16,704
This one has no deadline.
It's for an oil painting.

418
00:41:18,038 --> 00:41:19,123
How big is it?

419
00:41:19,206 --> 00:41:21,083
Well, it's about…

420
00:41:21,166 --> 00:41:22,418
About this big?

421
00:41:22,501 --> 00:41:25,129
Or maybe this big?

422
00:41:29,091 --> 00:41:30,509
Please give me five minutes.

423
00:41:33,637 --> 00:41:34,680
Sorry?

424
00:41:46,525 --> 00:41:47,401
What on earth?

425
00:41:55,284 --> 00:41:57,703
-This is it.
-Do you live close by?

426
00:41:57,786 --> 00:41:59,872
-Yes.
-I'll…

427
00:41:59,955 --> 00:42:03,542
This is the first painting I ever bought.

428
00:42:03,626 --> 00:42:06,086
It dropped on the floor
when its string broke,

429
00:42:07,463 --> 00:42:09,423
and the frame was smashed.

430
00:42:09,506 --> 00:42:13,052
I've never worked with a painting before.
It really is huge.

431
00:42:13,135 --> 00:42:15,179
Good. I wanted a completely new frame.

432
00:42:16,513 --> 00:42:18,140
Roughly, how big is it?

433
00:42:19,475 --> 00:42:20,934
I don't have a measuring tape.

434
00:42:22,227 --> 00:42:23,937
No, it's okay.

435
00:42:24,021 --> 00:42:26,523
You can take actual measurements at home
and send them to me.

436
00:42:26,607 --> 00:42:27,775
Okay.

437
00:42:29,318 --> 00:42:31,070
Let me take a photo first.

438
00:42:31,737 --> 00:42:32,821
Is that okay?

439
00:42:44,166 --> 00:42:47,294
The restaurant's owner told me
the frame maker used to be a programmer.

440
00:42:47,378 --> 00:42:49,213
You're him, right?

441
00:42:49,296 --> 00:42:50,881
Which restaurant was it?

442
00:42:50,964 --> 00:42:53,550
The one under the study center.

443
00:42:53,634 --> 00:42:55,469
I see. Hyeong-seok's study center.

444
00:42:56,261 --> 00:42:57,971
Then, I guess that is me.

445
00:42:58,055 --> 00:43:01,350
So that was what you used to do. I see.

446
00:43:01,433 --> 00:43:02,976
Why? Did something happen?

447
00:43:05,312 --> 00:43:06,980
Well, as for me,

448
00:43:07,064 --> 00:43:08,565
stuff happened at home,

449
00:43:08,649 --> 00:43:10,442
and the frame that was fine for ten years

450
00:43:10,526 --> 00:43:12,361
fell on the floor when its string snapped.

451
00:43:12,444 --> 00:43:13,570
Isn't it strange?

452
00:43:15,364 --> 00:43:18,325
I guess such a question
would be bewildering since we just met.

453
00:43:19,243 --> 00:43:21,120
Well, nothing happened.

454
00:43:21,203 --> 00:43:23,580
And I get asked that all the time,
so I don't mind.

455
00:43:24,581 --> 00:43:26,542
I see. You get asked that all the time.

456
00:43:27,376 --> 00:43:28,460
It was…

457
00:43:29,545 --> 00:43:31,755
a strange day for me too.

458
00:43:32,798 --> 00:43:36,510
It was as if moments of the past
were coming together and…

459
00:43:38,011 --> 00:43:40,055
I'm not really good with words.

460
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:44,184
But there was a day like that.

461
00:43:55,446 --> 00:43:57,364
Are you sure you don't need any help?

462
00:43:58,115 --> 00:43:59,032
I'm sure.

463
00:44:28,937 --> 00:44:33,650
REOPENING AFTER RENOVATION
MAEUM STUDY CAFÉ

464
00:44:39,615 --> 00:44:41,742
Did you see that it's a study café now?

465
00:44:41,825 --> 00:44:43,243
Yes, I did.

466
00:44:43,744 --> 00:44:47,372
It looked very bright
after unblocking all the windows.

467
00:44:47,456 --> 00:44:50,375
Back then, making it dark
made it better to focus.

468
00:44:50,459 --> 00:44:51,627
But now, it's about openness.

469
00:44:51,710 --> 00:44:54,505
They concentrate better
with people going back and forth.

470
00:44:54,588 --> 00:44:56,590
Ma'am, it's me.

471
00:44:56,673 --> 00:44:58,717
-Hey.
-Two spicy stir-fried pork.

472
00:44:59,718 --> 00:45:00,844
It was that one.

473
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:03,013
You did that one.

474
00:45:03,096 --> 00:45:05,891
So you were the one
who told the owner here about my old job.

475
00:45:05,974 --> 00:45:07,935
What are you talking about
all of a sudden?

476
00:45:10,270 --> 00:45:11,605
Do you want to drink?

477
00:45:11,688 --> 00:45:13,190
This is rare.

478
00:45:13,273 --> 00:45:14,483
You're getting a call.

479
00:45:25,786 --> 00:45:26,912
No.

480
00:45:29,915 --> 00:45:33,335
-It was an unknown number.
-Why did you answer it then?

481
00:45:33,418 --> 00:45:36,296
-Ma'am, a rolled omelet too!
-Okay.

482
00:45:50,852 --> 00:45:52,354
For ten years, I'd forgotten.

483
00:45:53,647 --> 00:45:54,898
They were gone.

484
00:45:55,482 --> 00:45:58,026
But can old worries come back?

485
00:45:58,110 --> 00:46:00,821
If it's ten years ago,
that's after you got into college.

486
00:46:01,738 --> 00:46:03,657
Then, it's likely not about your family.

487
00:46:03,740 --> 00:46:06,410
You don't talk about the stuff
that really worries you.

488
00:46:07,786 --> 00:46:11,164
You were really going through it
before you did your military duty.

489
00:46:11,999 --> 00:46:13,709
It had to be about a girl,

490
00:46:13,792 --> 00:46:17,462
but you just wouldn't talk about it
because you said it would remind you.

491
00:46:17,546 --> 00:46:19,798
You said you'd die
if you spoke about it out loud.

492
00:46:19,881 --> 00:46:23,385
So if you're talking about it,
it's not a problem.

493
00:46:23,468 --> 00:46:25,345
If it's a real problem,
you never mention it.

494
00:46:25,429 --> 00:46:27,014
You're afraid it would worry you.

495
00:46:29,725 --> 00:46:31,101
Right.

496
00:46:31,184 --> 00:46:33,729
Geez. That was it.

497
00:46:34,563 --> 00:46:36,982
I've worked as the study center's
manager for ten years.

498
00:46:37,065 --> 00:46:41,612
I'm at the peak of encouraging
and counseling the kids who don't study.

499
00:46:41,695 --> 00:46:43,488
"You matter. It's up to you in the end."

500
00:46:43,572 --> 00:46:46,825
"That guy lives his life
on his own terms."

501
00:46:46,908 --> 00:46:49,036
"He can't hold his liquor,
but whenever he drinks,

502
00:46:49,119 --> 00:46:51,705
he only thinks about what to do
and his direction in life."

503
00:46:51,788 --> 00:46:54,166
"You should focus on that too."

504
00:46:54,249 --> 00:46:57,044
"And he got into
Hanguk National University."

505
00:46:57,127 --> 00:47:00,130
"He used to sit in Seat One."
I end with promoting the study center.

506
00:47:01,715 --> 00:47:05,594
So, stop bringing back old worries.

507
00:47:05,677 --> 00:47:06,762
Okay?

508
00:47:06,845 --> 00:47:10,140
Did you already forget the kind of future
your mom wished for you?

509
00:47:11,224 --> 00:47:14,227
"Something safe and peaceful."

510
00:47:15,687 --> 00:47:17,939
I'm making that my family motto
when I get married.

511
00:47:18,774 --> 00:47:20,651
Then, memorize it properly.

512
00:47:22,778 --> 00:47:24,738
This sure is peaceful.

513
00:47:32,621 --> 00:47:33,997
"Something safe and peaceful

514
00:47:36,124 --> 00:47:38,335
where he can make a living
without struggle."

515
00:47:42,923 --> 00:47:47,052
JANUARY 2022

516
00:47:47,135 --> 00:47:48,428
Tae-seo.

517
00:47:48,512 --> 00:47:49,888
Yes?

518
00:47:49,971 --> 00:47:51,473
You've been dispatched

519
00:47:52,432 --> 00:47:54,184
to the India branch.

520
00:47:54,267 --> 00:47:57,354
We've worked with their research team,
so there will be familiar faces.

521
00:47:58,188 --> 00:47:59,189
It's a good opportunity.

522
00:48:00,023 --> 00:48:01,483
Yes, sir. I understand.

523
00:48:05,278 --> 00:48:07,114
It's not a big deal.

524
00:48:07,197 --> 00:48:09,991
But Grandpa fell
on his behind while weeding.

525
00:48:10,075 --> 00:48:12,536
The village head said he fainted.

526
00:48:12,619 --> 00:48:14,121
But he's just taking aspirin.

527
00:48:14,204 --> 00:48:16,415
He should… He should go to the hospital.

528
00:48:17,874 --> 00:48:20,794
Make him get a prescription for medicine.
I'll drop by this weekend.

529
00:48:20,877 --> 00:48:23,213
Don't worry.
Just visit during Lunar New Year.

530
00:48:23,296 --> 00:48:26,049
Busy people only come
on Lunar New Year and Chuseok.

531
00:48:26,133 --> 00:48:29,761
Things are running well around here
thanks to me. But it won't last.

532
00:48:29,845 --> 00:48:31,346
Enjoy your freedom.

533
00:48:33,932 --> 00:48:35,809
I saw Auntie Suk-hui today.

534
00:48:35,892 --> 00:48:38,603
Mom used to work with her at the station.

535
00:48:38,687 --> 00:48:42,566
She told me that I resembled Mom
whenever she'd get off work and say,

536
00:48:42,649 --> 00:48:44,317
"I love looking at the ocean."

537
00:48:44,401 --> 00:48:46,403
-It was a strange day.
-I guess I resemble Mom.

538
00:48:47,863 --> 00:48:50,323
In the morning, I received an opportunity.

539
00:48:50,407 --> 00:48:53,910
I heard Hui-seo talk about Mom
when he usually doesn't.

540
00:48:54,786 --> 00:48:59,040
And in the afternoon, I gave up
the opportunity I received in the morning.

541
00:48:59,124 --> 00:49:00,917
You don't want me to look into that room?

542
00:49:01,001 --> 00:49:03,462
Even though it's uphill,
it's a good price.

543
00:49:03,545 --> 00:49:06,590
-Actually, I want you to look into it.
-The next stop is Dongjak.

544
00:49:06,673 --> 00:49:08,633
-Hey, I'll call you back. Bye.
-The door is on…

545
00:49:15,515 --> 00:49:17,809
-The doors are closing.
-Hey, Hyeong-seok.

546
00:49:17,893 --> 00:49:20,479
-The doors are closing.
-Could you look into that room for me?

547
00:49:21,980 --> 00:49:24,941
I just got off the subway.
I couldn't hear a thing before.

548
00:49:27,944 --> 00:49:31,323
Well, something came up in the morning.

549
00:49:32,324 --> 00:49:33,325
Yeah.

550
00:49:34,242 --> 00:49:35,494
Okay, bye.

551
00:49:50,467 --> 00:49:55,639
At that moment,
I had a strong feeling that I knew

552
00:49:55,722 --> 00:49:57,641
what was important to me.

553
00:49:57,724 --> 00:49:59,309
Mom!

554
00:50:00,310 --> 00:50:01,561
Tae-seo!

555
00:50:04,022 --> 00:50:06,983
Compared to how much Mom cared for me…

556
00:50:07,067 --> 00:50:08,151
Wait just a bit.

557
00:50:08,235 --> 00:50:10,821
I didn't even care
a tiny fraction for myself.

558
00:50:13,907 --> 00:50:14,991
"Where?"

559
00:50:16,159 --> 00:50:18,495
In case something happens at home,

560
00:50:18,578 --> 00:50:20,914
a distance that can be traveled in a day.

561
00:50:23,667 --> 00:50:25,752
Later on one day,

562
00:50:26,795 --> 00:50:28,296
I'll be doing what I want to do.

563
00:50:29,714 --> 00:50:30,882
"With who?"

564
00:50:32,592 --> 00:50:33,593
Myself.

565
00:50:35,679 --> 00:50:37,514
The one momentarily free
thanks to Hui-seo.

566
00:50:39,558 --> 00:50:40,725
With myself.

567
00:50:43,895 --> 00:50:44,896
Will it be possible?

568
00:51:18,388 --> 00:51:25,020
CHONGSHIN UNIV (ISU)

569
00:51:30,066 --> 00:51:31,026
March.

570
00:51:31,818 --> 00:51:35,280
Every time around the start
of the school year, I thought of you.

571
00:51:38,783 --> 00:51:42,746
On the day of your parents' memorial,
I thought you'd be sad.

572
00:51:45,832 --> 00:51:47,167
I would think,

573
00:51:48,209 --> 00:51:49,669
"Should I call you?"

574
00:51:50,712 --> 00:51:52,339
And then, April would come.

575
00:51:53,632 --> 00:51:55,759
When summer comes, I can't do it.

576
00:51:56,635 --> 00:51:58,845
When autumn comes, it gets even harder.

577
00:52:00,597 --> 00:52:03,558
In the winter, I completely give up.

578
00:52:06,186 --> 00:52:08,146
I've repeated this for several years.

579
00:52:11,733 --> 00:52:13,360
But I'll stop now.

580
00:52:15,278 --> 00:52:17,030
Because I saw you.

581
00:52:20,867 --> 00:52:22,243
MESSAGE FROM CORNER STORE GRANNY

582
00:52:23,119 --> 00:52:24,955
Tae-seo is worried about you.

583
00:52:27,666 --> 00:52:30,043
010-0922-1109
YEON TAE-SEO

584
00:52:53,274 --> 00:52:54,359
MISSED CALL

585
00:52:59,239 --> 00:53:01,032
CALLS

586
00:53:25,682 --> 00:53:26,725
Hello?

587
00:53:29,811 --> 00:53:32,647
Sorry to call at this hour,
but I had a missed call.

588
00:53:34,607 --> 00:53:35,608
It's me.

589
00:53:39,654 --> 00:53:42,032
Why are you worried about me?

590
00:53:42,115 --> 00:53:44,617
That's what
the corner store granny told me.

591
00:53:49,456 --> 00:53:50,582
Are you outside?

592
00:53:55,045 --> 00:53:56,046
Yeah.

593
00:54:01,051 --> 00:54:04,763
Can I call you back in a little bit?

594
00:54:04,846 --> 00:54:06,389
Okay.

595
00:54:50,391 --> 00:54:51,226
Hey.

596
00:54:54,145 --> 00:54:55,396
Hi.

597
00:54:57,732 --> 00:55:00,193
You're a train operator, right?

598
00:55:01,111 --> 00:55:04,489
The corner store granny told me
you were a train operator in Seoul.

599
00:55:05,406 --> 00:55:07,617
Do you commute to Isu Station?

600
00:55:08,326 --> 00:55:11,412
-I heard it's different for each operator.
-It's Dongjak Station.

601
00:55:13,039 --> 00:55:14,582
I see.

602
00:55:17,710 --> 00:55:19,921
Train Operator Yeon Tae-seo.

603
00:55:21,172 --> 00:55:22,715
It suits you.

604
00:55:27,679 --> 00:55:29,931
I called to tell you
not to worry about me.

605
00:55:30,014 --> 00:55:32,976
My situation wasn't good,

606
00:55:33,059 --> 00:55:35,103
so that might've made you worry.

607
00:55:37,981 --> 00:55:39,607
What kind of situation was it?

608
00:55:42,110 --> 00:55:44,070
He wants to apologize to me.

609
00:55:44,654 --> 00:55:46,447
We had some stuff going on.

610
00:55:46,531 --> 00:55:47,824
It's a long story.

611
00:55:47,907 --> 00:55:49,742
He's your colleague from the hotel, right?

612
00:55:52,120 --> 00:55:53,955
Be clear with him.

613
00:55:55,957 --> 00:55:57,667
That way, he won't show up out of the blue

614
00:55:59,544 --> 00:56:01,087
to apologize.

615
00:56:04,382 --> 00:56:07,177
-If it's nothing to worry about--
-It's not.

616
00:56:07,260 --> 00:56:08,511
Don't worry.

617
00:56:14,267 --> 00:56:16,186
Okay. It's late.

618
00:56:16,269 --> 00:56:18,688
-I'll hang up now.
-Okay.

619
00:56:39,500 --> 00:56:41,461
NO ANSWERING THE PHONE AFTER WORK HOURS

620
00:56:55,433 --> 00:56:56,559
Hello, sir.

621
00:56:56,643 --> 00:56:58,061
You can't stay there.

622
00:56:58,144 --> 00:57:00,897
Please stick to the contract.
It's supposed to be an unmanned hotel.

623
00:57:00,980 --> 00:57:02,440
I'm sorry.

624
00:57:02,523 --> 00:57:03,983
I came in a hurry, so…

625
00:57:04,692 --> 00:57:06,444
I have a place to stay
starting from today.

626
00:57:06,527 --> 00:57:08,154
It seems one of the customers saw you.

627
00:57:08,780 --> 00:57:11,491
They asked me
if it really is an unmanned hotel.

628
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:15,620
Please follow the rules,
or you'll put me in a tough position.

629
00:57:22,585 --> 00:57:23,795
Eun-a.

630
00:57:24,879 --> 00:57:27,465
-I'm not late, am I?
-Not at all.

631
00:57:27,549 --> 00:57:30,927
I heard you got to Isu Station that day
but had to go back because of work.

632
00:57:31,010 --> 00:57:33,304
It would've been great
if we had dinner together then.

633
00:57:34,597 --> 00:57:37,934
-Ho-sik, Eun-a's here!
-I'm coming.

634
00:57:38,017 --> 00:57:40,687
-Did you bring the camera and batteries?
-Yeah.

635
00:57:40,770 --> 00:57:42,480
-I got everything. We're good.
-Good.

636
00:57:45,191 --> 00:57:47,318
Traveling is our job,

637
00:57:47,402 --> 00:57:51,155
but our dog and plants
made it hard to go on long trips.

638
00:57:51,239 --> 00:57:53,241
We're lucky to just have
the plants looked after.

639
00:57:53,324 --> 00:57:55,201
We can be away for a while
thanks to Eun-a.

640
00:57:55,285 --> 00:57:56,327
That's right.

641
00:57:56,411 --> 00:57:58,788
It's nothing.
I'm the one who's truly grateful.

642
00:57:59,664 --> 00:58:00,999
You saved me.

643
00:58:01,833 --> 00:58:03,585
Come on. Let's go.

644
00:58:03,668 --> 00:58:05,503
She was waiting to see you.

645
00:58:05,587 --> 00:58:07,630
Hurry and get going.

646
00:58:07,714 --> 00:58:09,132
Please enjoy your trip.

647
00:58:09,215 --> 00:58:11,551
What was that?
You sound like a hotel manager.

648
00:58:14,178 --> 00:58:16,180
Take care of our place for us.

649
00:58:16,264 --> 00:58:17,682
-Have a good trip.
-Bye.

650
00:58:17,765 --> 00:58:18,600
Let's go!

651
00:58:18,683 --> 00:58:21,269
Let's go! We're late!

652
00:58:55,887 --> 00:58:56,888
Dongjak Station.

653
00:59:43,976 --> 00:59:45,812
The screen doors are opening.

654
01:00:05,498 --> 01:00:06,874
The doors are closing.

655
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:09,210
The doors are closing.

656
01:00:09,293 --> 01:00:10,837
The screen doors are closing.

657
01:00:10,920 --> 01:00:12,797
Please stand back.

658
01:03:37,543 --> 01:03:38,878
It's been a while.

659
01:03:55,227 --> 01:03:58,731
STILL SHINING

660
01:04:24,840 --> 01:04:26,342
You really haven't changed.

661
01:04:26,425 --> 01:04:29,345
It's the same. My feelings are the same.

662
01:04:31,764 --> 01:04:34,058
You're someone I liked ten years ago,

663
01:04:34,600 --> 01:04:36,018
but I still feel the same way.

664
01:04:36,102 --> 01:04:38,312
All the things you see every day in Seoul,

665
01:04:38,396 --> 01:04:39,730
I want to see too.

666
01:04:39,814 --> 01:04:41,482
Stay right by my side.

667
01:04:41,565 --> 01:04:42,984
Granny!

668
01:04:43,901 --> 01:04:46,862
You just take back what's yours
and go back to living your life.

669
01:04:47,488 --> 01:04:48,656
Is he…

670
01:04:49,824 --> 01:04:51,117
weighing on you a lot?

671
01:04:57,498 --> 01:04:59,500
Subtitle translation by: Hye Won Yoon
